  "title": "BUSINESS DEVELOPMENT MANAGER",
  "description": "<p>The Business Development Manager is responsible for driving business growth, increasing revenue, and expanding the company’s market presence. The role involves identifying new business opportunities, developing strategic partnerships, strengthening customer relationships, and implementing marketing and sales initiatives to support the expansion of the barber and grooming services business.</p><p>Key responsibilities include developing and executing business development strategies, analysing market trends, identifying new customer segments, and creating promotional campaigns to increase brand visibility. The Business Development Manager will work closely with operations and management teams to improve service offerings, pricing strategies, and customer experience.</p><p>The role also involves managing corporate and retail client accounts, negotiating contracts, monitoring sales performance, preparing business proposals, and ensuring sustainable revenue growth. The Business Development Manager will support outlet expansion, franchising opportunities (if applicable), and partnerships with malls, hotels, corporates, and lifestyle brands.</p><h2><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></h2><ul><li><p>Identify and develop new business opportunities to increase company revenue</p></li><li><p>Build and maintain strong relationships with customers, partners, and corporate clients</p></li><li><p>Develop sales, marketing, and promotional strategies for barber and grooming services</p></li><li><p>Conduct market research and competitor analysis</p></li><li><p>Prepare business proposals, presentations, and reports for management</p></li><li><p>Negotiate pricing, contracts, and partnership agreements</p></li><li><p>Support outlet expansion, collaborations, and brand partnerships</p></li><li><p>Monitor sales performance and recommend improvement strategies</p></li><li><p>Coordinate with operations teams to align services with market demand</p></li><li><p>Ensure compliance with company policies and industry regulations</p></li></ul><h2><strong>Job Requirements</strong></h2><ul><li><p>Diploma or Degree in Business Administration, Marketing, Management, or related field</p></li><li><p>Minimum <strong>2–5 years</strong> of relevant experience in business development, sales, or marketing</p></li><li><p>Experience in <strong>retail, service, lifestyle, F&B, beauty, or grooming industry</strong> is an advantage</p></li><li><p>Strong communication, negotiation, and interpersonal skills</p></li><li><p>Ability to analyse market trends and develop growth strategies</p></li><li><p>Self-motivated, results-driven, and able to work independently</p></li><li><p>Proficient in Microsoft Office (Word, Excel, PowerPoint)</p></li><li><p>Good organisational and reporting skills</p></li></ul>",
